# Runbook

## 1. Detect
- Check CloudWatch Logs for each Lambda (`/aws/lambda/cost-security-*`).
- Review custom metrics: `CostSecurity/CollectedRecords`, `CostSecurity/CorrelatedSignals` (TODO).

## 2. Stabilize
- Re-run failed Lambda from AWS Console or via `sam remote invoke`.
- Enable DRY_RUN by setting `DRY_RUN=true` in environment variables to replay sample data.

## 3. Mitigate
- Use false-positive manager to suppress noisy signals temporarily.
- Rotate credentials or update IAM policies if access errors occur.

## 4. Restore
- Trigger CodePipeline redeploy after fixes (`Release` stage).
- Document incident summary and lessons learned in this runbook.

